The selected hypothesis is a refinement of the highest-performing existing model (`inner_loop_model`). Instead of relying on a normalized proportion (`imbalance`), this hypothesis proposes that humans use the raw, unnormalized count difference between heads and tails as their heuristic for sequence randomness. 

